As a consequence of the conservation of energy, the transmission coefficient (transmission) in each interface is given by T = 1 − R. Therefore, for reflection losses at all interfaces before the solar radiation reaches the CdTe absorber layer, the transmission T(λ) can be calculated by the formula4T(λ)=(1−R12)(1−R23)(1−R34)(1−R45),\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
